A motorcyclist who died in a crash in Carmarthenshire has been named as Philip Venn.The 60-year-old was riding on the A40 between Llandovery and Llanwrda shortly after 13:00 BST on Wednesday when he was involved in a collision.His family and friends issued a statement saying he will be dearly missed.Dyfed-Powys Police has appealed for witnesses.
"On Wednesday 12th June 2024 Philip George Venn was killed in a road traffic accident on the A40 whilst out for a ride on his motorbike," said Mr Venn's family, adding details of his funeral would be released shortly."Phil has left behind loved ones and friends who will dearly miss him," they said.Investigating officers said they would particularly like to speak to any motorists who were in the area at the time of the crash who have a dashcam in their vehicles.
